issue.title: sharepoint-crud  operation on my  personal site url
issue.body:
Thank you for reporting an issue or suggesting an enhancement. We appreciate your feedback - to help the team to understand your needs, please complete the below template to ensure we have the necessary details to assist you. 

#### Category
- [ ] Question
- [ ] Bug

Desired Behavior
A webaprt added to a sitecollection1 which is performing SharePoint crud Operations  to a list in another sitecollection2
Below solution was used  ,  and  this.context.pageContext.web.absoluteUrl was hardcoded with sitecollection2 URL 
Reference :- https://github.com/SharePoint/sp-dev-fx-webparts/blob/master/samples/sharepoint-crud/src/webparts/noFrameworkCrud/NoFrameworkCrudWebPart.ts

Expected Behavior
The solution works for any other siteollection except for mypersonal site 
https://xxx-my.sharepoint.com/personal/xxx_xxx_onmicrosoft_com/ URL

#### Observed Behavior
-Item 'undefined' (ID: undefined) successfully created on Create Item
https://xxx-my.sharepoint.com/personal/xxx_xxx_onmicrosoft_com/_api/web/lists/getbytitle('ListName')/items?$select=Title,Id 403 Forbidden from console
https://xxx-my.sharepoint.com/personal/xxx_xxx_onmicrosoft_com/_api/web/lists/getbytitle('ListName')/items 403 Forbidden from console
But I am able to  Access Rest URL from the browser 

Thanks,

comment.body:
Hello... sorry to bring this up... but I have exactly the same problem described by Jiannko.
I got a 403 forbidden querying a list in my personal site using REST. The rest url in the browser works fine and the rest url for other site collections works fine too.

Jiannko, how did you resolve this?

Thanks.

issue.title: Wordpress with Sharepoint
issue.body:
Dear Team,
I need your help to know how to display a new on landing page in sharepoint from website created in wordpress. We have news which is in a website(wordpress), I need that to be displayed in Sharepoint page.,
How can this be achived.

comment.body:
> Thanks for you answer. This will help me a lot. Also if I need to display the image from the new, can this be possible from this RSS reader

I believe so but we havent done this part ourselves (yet). This will require some customisation of your RSS feed from Wordpress as well as creating a custom template on the web part, if you google this there are a few articles on how to do this.

Bear in mind that you may encounter some CORS issues which you may need to ensure your WP site is allowing CORS requests.

issue.title: Wordpress with Sharepoint
issue.body:
Dear Team,
I need your help to know how to display a new on landing page in sharepoint from website created in wordpress. We have news which is in a website(wordpress), I need that to be displayed in Sharepoint page.,
How can this be achived.

comment.body:
> Dear Team,
> I need your help to know how to display a new on landing page in sharepoint from website created in wordpress. We have news which is in a website(wordpress), I need that to be displayed in Sharepoint page.,
> How can this be achived.

Not really an issue - however, you can do this by:
1) Installing the react-rss-reader sample
2) Using this web part on your sharepoint page, choose Direct Feed and on whatever news page you are on on Wordpress add "/feed" at the end of the url (e.g. if your news page is https://www.somenews.com/news, put in https://www.somenews.com/news/feed).

We do this successfully.

issue.title: react-carousel web part image not getting loaded
issue.body:
https://github.com/SharePoint/sp-dev-docs/issues/new

when i run react-carousel web part and choose my image library , the images are not getting loaded in webpart

Thanks for your contribution! Sharing is caring.

comment.body:
Also by not getting loaded you see "loading image" spinner or empty webpart?
In any case i would say were is number of issues could happen with this solution
some things i can see already:
1. beta versions of spfx framwork used
2. Specifically filtering image library type (109) which might not be available for example in communication sites with out of the box settings.

Web part it self is quite simple and nice, but i would recommend either rebuild with latest spfx or look for other example.
